<Author>kauerman
<Content>Plastic Cube as bathroom !! First the good things about the Allegra, the location is superb, just at Bahnhof Friedrichstrasse, but in a silent street with lots of restaurants around. However, the quality of the hotel itself is (friendly speaking) borderline. Instead of a bathroom the rooms are equipped with a plastic cube with a little more than 1squared meter size (including toilet, shower and sink). It means, you basically have the toilet under the shower. This is FAR below German standard I must say. Secondly, the breakfast room is tiny and there are not enough tables to fit all guests. Hence, you will have to squeeze yourself at any table, where there is a vacant seat, having breakfast with strangers at your table. The breakfast itself is excellent, but there the breakfast room does not provide an environment to appreciate this. Finally, schedule enough time to get to your room. A single tiny elevator serves the 80 rooms. All in all, I found this hotel disappointing, but the locationmakes up for some pitfalls. 
