<Author>fabri
<Content>perfect location, good functional hotel I spent five nights at Hotel Allegra during business travel early March. The tariff was fair price, so rather expensive but not too expenasive in comparison with other hotels in the city where some colleagues were hosted. Perfect location, close to UBahn und SBahn Friedrichstrasse, where all connections stop and go. Good restaurants, pubs or theatre are at a stone's throw (do not miss the Staendige Vertretung). At Friedrichstrasse station you get everything at any daytime: Berlin daily or 7days card, phone card, lunch or dinner, bread or cakes, a small market. The single room was at the sixth and highest floor, from the window I could have a look at the Reichstag Dome and the silent inner court. Room was large, bathroom small but functional. I used the room only for sleeping and changing clothes. I heard a noise in the night if leaving the window open. If shut, no noise. Breakfast in the -2 level was good and rich (at least for Italian habits), the staff was rather cold and not friendly. I forgot to say that Hotel Allegra is the dependance of Hotel Albrechtshof. Both belong to the Berliner Mission, so you can say a prayer in the small chapel in the main building. All at all I recommend Hotel Allegra. I heard comments from many colleagues complaining of position and services of their accommodation. Berlin is anstrengend, so hotel location is very important. 
